# UI Patterns

## Collapsible Sections

Use `<details class="section-panel">` for content that benefits from progressive disclosure: settings, history, secondary info, and alternative input paths. The class provides a left-side rotating chevron, bolder text, hover background, and top/bottom borders.

```erb
<details class="section-panel">
  <summary>Section Title</summary>
  ...content...
</details>
```

Do not use `<hr>` tags to visually separate `<details>` elements -- the `section-panel` borders handle this.

## One-Time Actions (Share, Export, etc.)

Do not use `<details>` for one-time actions like sharing or exporting. Use a button that opens a native `<dialog>` modal instead. This is more discoverable and matches user expectations for actions.

```erb
<button type="button" class="outline secondary" onclick="document.getElementById('my-dialog').showModal()">Share</button>
<dialog id="my-dialog">
  <article>
    <header>
      <button type="button" aria-label="Close" rel="prev" onclick="document.getElementById('my-dialog').close()"></button>
      <h3>Dialog Title</h3>
    </header>
    ...content...
  </article>
</dialog>
```

## Auto-Refreshing Pages

Do not use `<meta http-equiv="refresh">` to periodically reload a page. A meta refresh triggers a full browser navigation, which causes visible flicker as the entire page goes blank and re-renders from scratch.

Instead, use the `poll` Stimulus controller, which fetches fresh HTML in the background and swaps only the inner content of a wrapper element — no blank screen, no scroll-position reset.

```erb
<div class="my-page"
     data-controller="poll"
     data-poll-src-value="<%= request.path %>"
     data-poll-selector-value=".my-page"
     data-poll-interval-value="3000">
  ...content...
</div>
```

- `data-poll-interval-value` is in milliseconds (default 3000).
- The controller automatically pauses polling while a `<dialog>` inside the element is open.
